ZH: 我今天在考试中犯了一个严重的失误。
EN: I made a serious mistake in my exam today.

ZH: 他在比赛中常常犯一些低级的失误。
EN: He often makes some amateur mistakes in the game.

ZH: 别让失误影响你的信心。
EN: Don't let mistakes shake your confidence.

ZH: 这次事故是因为工人犯了失误。
EN: The accident was caused by a mistake made by the workers.

ZH: 请原谅我的失误，我是无意的。
EN: Please forgive my mistake, it was unintentional.

ZH: 这是一个不能犯失误的时刻。
EN: This is a moment where no mistakes can be made.

ZH: 他们的失误导致了这场失败。
EN: Their mistakes led to this failure.

ZH: 这是一个不可接受的失误。
EN: This is an unacceptable mistake.

ZH: 我们应该从失误中吸取教训。
EN: We should learn from our mistakes.

ZH: 这是一个致命的失误。
EN: This is a fatal mistake.

ZH: 不要因为小失误就气馁。
EN: Don't be discouraged by small mistakes.

ZH: 这是我犯的一个愚蠢的失误。
EN: This is a stupid mistake that I made.

ZH: 在竞争中犯失误是不可避免的。
EN: Making mistakes in competition is inevitable.

ZH: 他不断地纠正自己的失误。
EN: He keeps correcting his mistakes constantly.

ZH: 我感到很抱歉因为我的失误给您造成了困扰。
EN: I am very sorry for causing you trouble with my mistake.

ZH: 他太年轻了，所以犯了一些无法避免的失误。
EN: He is too young, so he made some inevitable mistakes.

ZH: 当组织犯了失误，领导就应该承担责任。
EN: When an organization makes a mistake, the leaders should take responsibility.

ZH: 别人的失误不应该成为你的借口。
EN: Other people's mistakes should not be your excuse.

ZH: 我们必须认真对待每一个失误，以免重蹈覆辙。
EN: We must take every mistake seriously to avoid repeating them.

ZH: 失误是在每一个人生活中都会发生的。
EN: Mistakes happen in everyone's life.
